usage: operator_generate.py [-h] [--rule-packs-dir RULE_PACKS_DIR]
                            [--config-dir CONFIG_DIR]
                            [--output-dir OUTPUT_DIR] [--namespace NAMESPACE]
                            [--api-version {v1alpha1,v1beta1}] [--gitops]
                            [--dry-run] [--json]
                            [--components {all,rules,alertmanager,servicemonitor}]
                            [--receiver-template {slack,pagerduty,email,teams,opsgenie,webhook}]
                            [--secret-name SECRET_NAME]
                            [--secret-key SECRET_KEY] [--kustomize]

Generate Kubernetes CRD YAML for Prometheus + Alertmanager (PrometheusRule, AlertmanagerConfig, ServiceMonitor)

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --rule-packs-dir RULE_PACKS_DIR
                        Rule packs directory (default rule-packs/)
  --config-dir CONFIG_DIR
                        Tenant config directory (default conf.d/)
  --output-dir OUTPUT_DIR
                        Output CRD directory (default operator-manifests/)
  --namespace NAMESPACE
                        Target namespace (default monitoring)
  --api-version {v1alpha1,v1beta1}
                        AlertmanagerConfig API version (default v1beta1)
  --gitops              Enable GitOps mode (sorted keys, no timestamps)
  --dry-run             Print output instead of writing files
  --json                Output results as JSON report
  --components {all,rules,alertmanager,servicemonitor}
                        Components to generate (all | rules | alertmanager |
                        servicemonitor)
  --receiver-template {slack,pagerduty,email,teams,opsgenie,webhook}
                        Receiver template type (slack | pagerduty | email |
                        teams | opsgenie | webhook)
  --secret-name SECRET_NAME
                        K8s Secret name (for receiver credential reference)
  --secret-key SECRET_KEY
                        Key within the K8s Secret (auto-inferred from receiver
                        type if omitted)
  --kustomize           Generate kustomization.yaml listing all CRD files as
                        resources
